bilingual.source: What did you wear and how did you breathe?
bilingual.target: 你穿了什么，怎么呼吸的？

bilingual.source: It means a lot to animals and humans, though – they need it to breathe!
bilingual.target: 不过，它对动物和人类来说意义重大——他们需要它来呼吸！

bilingual.source: Dolphins are mammals, like you are, and must swim to the surface to breathe air.
bilingual.target: 海豚是哺乳动物，就像你一样，必须游到水面呼吸空气。

bilingual.source: The snorkel allows you to breathe while swimming face down.
bilingual.target: 呼吸管让你在脸朝下游泳时可以呼吸。
你可以在室外呼吸新鲜空气。

list.abstract: 《Breathe》是Taylor Swift在专辑《Fearless》中的一首与ColbieCaillat合唱的美国抒情风格的流行歌曲，发行于 2008年10月21日。
breathe是著名韩国歌手权志龙（G-dragon）演唱的一首歌曲，歌曲收录于专辑《COUP D´ETAT [+ ONE OF A KIND & HEARTBREAKER]》中。

yingyinNormal.en: You're my real brother! I can't breathe!
yingyinNormal.zh: 你是我的真弟弟。我都没法呼吸了！

yingyinNormal.en: I dozed off. You breathe so deep when you sleep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我刚刚睡着了。你睡觉的时候呼吸很沉。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I got to breathe. That's still free, isn't it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，我得呼吸一下，这还是免费的吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Are you sure she wasn't trying to breathe life back into him?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你确定她不是在帮他做人工呼吸吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Pardon me, do you have gills, ma'am? So you can't breathe underwater?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你有鳃吗，夫人? 所以你在水里不能呼吸?

yingyinNormal.en: You can't breathe. You can't think. Least, not about anything but the pain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你没法呼吸，没法思考，只能感觉得到痛苦。

yingyinNormal.en: Earth's atmosphere is 80 percent nitrogen. We don't even breathe nitrogen.
yingyinNormal.zh: 地球的大气层80%都是氮气，可我们不呼吸氮气。

yingyinNormal.en: And you are all absolutely working as a team, don't you? Like breathe together. Yeah.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而且还要绝对地协调一致，是吗？连呼吸都要同步。对。

yingyinNormal.en: And nowadays you breathe, and you risk your life. Every moment now you don't have a choice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如今连呼吸都是在冒生命危险，现在我们别无选择。

yingyinNormal.en: Why would you have surgery? Because I can't breathe. I snore, I get sinus infections.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么要做手术？因为我呼吸不顺，打呼，还会鼻窦发炎。

yingyinNormal.en: Just remember to breathe up through your feathers and from your talons. Namaste. Bomb?
yingyinNormal.zh: 记住，要运用你的羽毛和你的爪子充分呼吸，我向你鞠躬致意，炸弹？

yingyinNormal.en: The only way we're going up there is if some fairy godmother shows up and helps us breathe air.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们上去的唯一可能是童话里的仙女出现然后赐予我们呼吸空气的能力。
yingyinNormal.videoNameEn: 《The SpongeBob Movie: Sponge Out of Water》

yingyinNormal.en: Reggie, you'll take the car to and from school. I like the air, okay? I like to breathe in the air.
yingyinNormal.zh: 雷吉，你必须坐车上下学。我喜欢外面的空气，我喜欢呼吸外面的空气。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay, I can breathe again. Babe, they want to have sex. Oh, of course! The annual birthday booty spectacular!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，我又能呼吸了。亲爱的，他们想做爱。当然啊，年度生日庆祝打炮大典！

yingyinNormal.en: He needs to drink.That's right. He needs to breathe a bit. Very good. He needs to sleep. Excellent.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他还需要喝水。说的对。他还需要呼吸新鲜空气。说的非常好。他还需要睡觉。你也说的很好。

yingyinNormal.en: Come on, Bernie, breathe. Remember what you learned in birthing class. I remember thinking, this is stupid, and I was right!
yingyinNormal.zh: 好了，妮妮，呼吸。还记得在生产课上学的吗。我记得我觉得这样做很傻逼，我是对的！

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, Bernie, I'd be thrilled. It's not be my birth coach. Okay, that hurts, but luckily I know how to breathe through it.
yingyinNormal.zh: 妮妮，我会高兴死的。不是要叫你当我的生育教练。伤心了，但幸好我懂如何调整呼吸撑过去。

yingyinNormal.en: You know what? The doctor will be in soon, why don't we not speak until then. Seriously, breathe louder, Ross. That's great.
yingyinNormal.zh: 医生马上到，在那之前，我们还是别说话。说真的，呼吸再大声一点，罗斯，那真的太棒了。

yingyinNormal.en: Excuse me. Evolution is not for you to buy, Phoebe. Evolution is scientific fact, like the air we breathe, like gravity.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对不起，进化论不是信不信由你，菲比，进化论是科学事实，就像我们呼吸的空气就像地心引力。

yingyinNormal.en: I've had 27 surgeries since then. They've helped me to breathe, to see, to hear without a hearing aid, and some even helped me look a bit better.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我出生后做了27次手术。为了让我正常呼吸，恢复视力，摆脱助听器，让我变得更好看一些。

examination_example.sentence: Hidalgo also has supported a "Paris <highlight>Breathes</highlight>" day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 伊达尔戈还支持了“巴黎呼吸日”。

examination_example.sentence: Although ebikes first appeared in the 90s, cheaper options and longer-lasting batteries are <highlight>breathing</highlight> new life into the concept.
